A BILL ENTITLED
1 AN ACT concerning
2 Maryland Forestry Education Fund – Mandatory Funding – Extension
3 FOR the purpose of extending the fiscal years in which the Governor is required to include
4 a certain appropriation in the annual budget bill for the Maryland Forestry
5 Education Fund; and generally relating to the Maryland Forestry Education Fund.
6 BY repealing and reenacting, with amendments,
7 Article – Natural Resources
8 Section 5–2001
9 Annotated Code of Maryland
10 (2023 Replacement Volume and 2024 Supplement)
11 SECTION 1. BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF MARYLAND,
12 That the Laws of Maryland read as follows:
13 Article – Natural Resources
14 5–2001.
15 (a) In this section, “Fund” means the Maryland Forestry Education Fund.
16 (b) There is a Maryland Forestry Education Fund.
17 (c) The purpose of the Fund is to expand and enhance:
18 (1) The Maryland Forestry Foundation’s capacity to provide education and
19 resources that support Maryland’s forest landowners;
20 (2) The ability of district forestry boards and the knowledge of local
21 governments in Maryland to achieve:
