1 (i) Environmental, economic, and social sustainability of forest
2 health; and
3 (ii) The sustainable management of forest resources; and
4 (3) The ability of businesses to test innovative best management practices
5 in forestry.
6 (d) The Maryland Forestry Foundation shall administer the Fund.
7 (e) (1) The Fund is a special, nonlapsing fund that is not subject to § 7–302 of
8 the State Finance and Procurement Article.
9 (2) The State Treasurer shall hold the Fund separately, and the
10 Comptroller shall account for the Fund.
11 (f) The Fund consists of:
12 (1) Money appropriated in the State budget to the Fund;
13 (2) Interest earnings; and
14 (3) Any other money from any other source accepted for the benefit of the
15 Fund.
16 (g) The Fund may be used only for:
17 (1) Providing training and education to forest landowners, district forestry
18 boards, and local governments to ensure the landowners, boards, and governments are well
19 informed on advances and developments in:
20 (i) Healthy forest management;
21 (ii) Ecological service markets;
22 (iii) Emerging forestry threats;
23 (iv) Climate science;
24 (v) Forest conservation;
25 (vi) Urban forestry;
26 (vii) Sustainability science;
27 (viii) Forestry policy;

